.TH "srcu_readers_active" 9 "srcu_readers_active" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
srcu_readers_active \- returns true if there are readers. and false otherwise
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" srcu_readers_active
.BI "(struct srcu_struct *ssp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
which srcu_struct to count active readers (holding srcu_read_lock).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that this is not an atomic primitive, and can therefore suffer
severe errors when invoked on an active srcu_struct.  That said, it
can be useful as an error check at cleanup time.
